snippet.title: Elon Musk Offered Amber Heard 24*7 Security [ Johnny Depp and Amber Heard Trial ]
snippet.description:
Elon Musk Offered Amber Heard 24*7 Security [ Johnny Depp and Amber Heard Trial ]

Elon Musk offered Amber Heard "every minute of every day security" after she revealed to him she needed a controlling request against Johnny Depp, the High Court has heard. 

She denied Elon Musk visited her while her then-spouse Johnny Depp was away. 

Johnny Depp, is suing the distributor of the Sun over an article that marked him a "tank top" - yet the paper demands it was precise. 

The US entertainer, , was giving proof in London for a second day on the eleventh day of her ex's slander activity. 

She excused recommendations Elon Musk visited her in 2015 while Johnny Depp was away, saying she was not in contact with the Tesla author until the next year. 

On Tuesday, Depp's attorney, Eleanor Laws QC, addressed Ms Heard on her announcement, in which the legal advisor said the on-screen character had demonstrated that Johnny Depp was "strangely desirous" and that she wasn't having any "unlawful connections". 

The preliminary adjudicator, Justice Nicol, interceded to state "unlawful... conveys an undertone". 

Golden Heard answered: "Not that that issues a lot, however no." 

Ms Laws concurred: "No, it doesn't. 

The legal advisor at that point read out instant messages between Amber Heard and elon Musk from 22 May 2016, in which Ms Heard told elon Musk that she would acquire a controlling request against her at that point spouse. 

The messages came a day after a supposed occurrence at the Eastern Columbia Building in Los Angeles, where Johnny Depp and golden Heard lived, in which the entertainer claims Depp tossed her cell phone at her, smacking her in the face - which the on-screen character denies. 

Addressing amber Heard, Mis Laws said elon Musk offered to "orchestrate day in and day out security for you", including that he stated: "The offer would stand, regardless of whether you never needed to see me again... anyway, upset for being a simpleton. The radio quiet damages a great deal. It just issues since I truly like you." 

The lawyer at that point alluded to prove given by Alejandro Romero, an attendant at the Eastern Columbia Building, who said he saw Musk visiting Heard "when Johnny Depp was in Australia". 

Heard said Mr Romero was "off-base", demanding that she wasn't in correspondence with elon Musk until 2016. 

In his composed observer articulation, Romero stated: "From March 2015 onwards, Ms Heard was visited normally late around evening time, at around 11pm to 12 PM, by Elon Musk." 

The attendant asserted Heard gave Musk his own coxcomb to get to the structure.
